Three traffic officers were arrested by EACC detectives on Tuesday for soliciting bribes from motorists on Kiserian-Ngong road.The officers were arrested for allegedly asking for and taking bribes from matatu operators and truck drivers.The detectives confiscated several notes in various denominations from them.The officers were taken to Ngong police station where the traffic base commander was also grilled.Ngong OCPD George Seda told the Star on phone that he could not comment on the arrests as he was in a meeting.Read: Matatu owners say they lose Sh3bn yearly to traffic officers